---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Regulations (EN)"
  description="Badge regulations for Beskidzki Włóczykij — rules for earning and verification."
>

  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Badge Regulations</h1>
      <p>Rules for earning the Beskidzki Włóczykij badge</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="content-section">
    <div class="container content-body">

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 1</h2>
        <p>
          The "BESKIDZKI WŁÓCZYKIJ" badge has been established by the Board of the Upper
          Silesian Branch of the Polish Tourist and Sightseeing Society (PTTK) in Katowice.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 2</h2>
        <p>
          The aim of establishing the "BESKIDZKI WŁÓCZYKIJ" badge is to promote tourism in the
          Beskid Mountains and to encourage the exploration of their historical, cultural and
          natural values, especially in less known and less frequently visited areas, both within
          Poland and beyond its borders.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 3</h2>
        <p>
          The "BESKIDZKI WŁÓCZYKIJ" badge may be earned by anyone, regardless of age or
          nationality.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 4</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>
            The "BESKIDZKI WŁÓCZYKIJ" badge is earned by climbing mountain peaks located in the
            Beskid Mountains within the territory of four countries: Poland, the Czech Republic,
            Slovakia and Ukraine.
          </li>
          <li>
            Climbing peaks located in a country affected by ongoing military conflict is not
            required, and the authors of the project strongly advise against undertaking such
            activity.
          </li>
          <li>
            The badge is earned at one's own risk, during hiking trips in mountainous terrain,
            in accordance with applicable safety rules and regulations governing protected and
            private areas. Participants are required to follow the principles of safe and
            responsible mountain tourism.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 5</h2>
        <p>The badge has three levels (bronze, silver and gold).</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The <strong>bronze</strong> level is awarded after completing any <strong>50 peaks</strong> listed in the official register.</li>
          <li>The <strong>silver</strong> level is awarded after completing a further 50 listed peaks, i.e. a total of <strong>100 peaks</strong>.</li>
          <li>The <strong>gold</strong> level is awarded after completing all <strong>150 peaks</strong> listed in the register, subject to the provisions of § 4.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 6</h2>
        <p>
          Peaks completed prior to the first edition of this publication, i.e. before 1 March
          2026, may be included towards the badge.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 7</h2>
        <p>There is no time limit for completing the badge.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 8</h2>
        <p>The order in which the peaks are completed is optional.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 9</h2>
        <p>
          The sole basis for verification is the official "BESKIDZKI WŁÓCZYKIJ" badge booklet,
          maintained by the participant and containing confirmation of completion of all required
          peaks.
        </p>
        <p>Proof of completion may include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>a stamp from the summit or its immediate vicinity,</li>
          <li>a photograph of the participant taken on the summit, inserted into the booklet,</li>
          <li>
            confirmation (signature or stamp) by a PTTK mountain tourism leader or a licensed
            mountain guide, together with the number of a valid ID card or licence,
          </li>
          <li>
            electronic verification is permitted. A participant who has purchased the official
            badge booklet may submit photographic documentation confirming the completion of
            peaks to the e-mail address indicated by the verification committee. Detailed rules
            for electronic verification, including required documentation, are published on the
            project website: <strong>www.beskidzkiwloczykij.pl</strong>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The participant's full name and the dates of completion of individual peaks must be
          entered in the booklet.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 10</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>
            After collecting all required confirmations, the badge booklet is submitted for
            verification at the headquarters of the Upper Silesian Branch of PTTK in Katowice.
          </li>
          <li>
            The participant covers the cost of a possible badge purchase as well as postal costs
            related to verification.
          </li>
          <li>
            Participants who complete any level of the badge may purchase a unique "BESKIDZKI
            WŁÓCZYKIJ" badge.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 11</h2>
        <p>
          Upon successful verification, a stamp confirming the awarding of the given badge level
          is placed in the designated area of the booklet, together with the signature of a
          member of the verification committee.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 12</h2>
        <p>
          A verified booklet serves as an official certificate of the awarded badge level and
          entitles the holder to purchase and wear the badge.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 13</h2>
        <p>
          The badge may be purchased at the headquarters of the Upper Silesian Branch of PTTK
          in Katowice upon presentation of a verified booklet or, in the case of electronic
          verification, via postal delivery.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 14</h2>
        <p>
          By applying for the badge, the participant consents to the processing of personal data
          required for the purpose of badge verification, in accordance with applicable
          regulations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 15</h2>
        <p>
          Any doubts arising from the interpretation of these regulations shall be resolved by
          the verification committee of the badge.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 16</h2>
        <p>
          These regulations were adopted by resolution of the Board of the Upper Silesian Branch
          of PTTK in Katowice on 4 December 2025 and enter into force on that date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 17</h2>
        <p>
          The right to interpret these regulations in matters not expressly covered herein rests
          with the verification committee, after consultation with the authors of the project.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="reg-section">
        <h2>§ 18</h2>
        <p>
          The "BESKIDZKI WŁÓCZYKIJ" badge booklet constitutes a separate publication. Its
          distribution is conducted by the publisher and other cooperating entities, in
          accordance with general principles.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>

<style>
  .content-body { max-width: 720px; }
  .reg-section {
    margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
    padding-top: 1.2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--clr-border);
  }
  .reg-section:first-child { border-top: none; }
  .reg-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin-bottom: .6rem;
    color: var(--clr-accent);
  }
  .reg-section p  { color: var(--clr-muted); margin-bottom: .7rem; line-height: 1.75; }
  .reg-section ol,
  .reg-section ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--clr-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: .7rem;
  }
  .reg-section li { margin-bottom: .4rem; }
</style>
